 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Vice President, Data & Analytics Sutter Health 1,639 reviews Mather, CA Full-time Sutter Health 1,639 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Position Overview: 
The Vice President, Data and Analytics reports to the Chief Information Officer and provides leadership and strategic direction on improved analytics and reporting capabilities across inpatient and ambulatory care environments that support Sutter Health’s goal of driving quality and efficiency across the continuum of care. Provides leadership on integrated care networks analytics needs on information integration and sharing with various stakeholders, to improve care coordination and decrease population care gaps. Serves as principal analytics champion within the organization. 
Qualifications: 
Education:
 Bachelor’s degree required; Master’s degree preferred. 
Experience: 
10+ years’ progressive leadership experience with large scale data analysis and outcome evaluation experience required 
Healthcare experience is highly preferred 
Extensive experience in developing strategy around data architecture, building teams and standardization 
Experience in risk and non-risk delivery model is highly preferred 
Experience working in advanced data science (e.g. machine learning, predictive analysis, AI) and ability to select right data solutions for business needs 
Experience creating and leading within a complex cloud-based environment using established methods such as Agile 
Knowledge: 
Business acumen on healthcare market trends and associated data and intelligence tool supporting needs 
Demonstrated knowledge of quality improvement theory and practice 
Skills: 
Proficiency in statistical methodologies 
Experience in module design, defining requirements, project risks and create strategies for risk mitigation and contingency planning 
Demonstrated ability managing multiple processes, resources and projects in a manner that will maximize efficiency and productivity 
Strong mathematical, analytical and technical skills 
Strong organizational and conflict resolution skills.
 Excellent communication and interpersonal skills 
Strong leadership acumen with team management experience 
Organization: Sutter Health System Office 
 Employee Status:  Regular 
 Employee Referral Bonus:  No 
